Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.50,0:04:19.97,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Takerō Meiwa (22)\NPart-time Worker
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.22,0:00:03.48,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}'The Red Oily {\i1}Pssht{\i0} Case.'
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.48,0:00:08.28,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That's what Yumi-{\i1}san{\i0} from the Metropolitan Police's Traffic Dept. called a serial car break-in case.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.28,0:00:11.07,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}After picking the lock and breaking into the cars,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.07,0:00:13.57,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}this vandal spray-paints the word 'Die!' on the ceiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.57,0:00:15.78,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It was a vicious case.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.78,0:00:18.37,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Officer Chiba's car was also attacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.37,0:00:22.79,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}So he called Yumi-{\i1}san{\i0}, who came by along with a rookie policewoman
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.79,0:00:26.38,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}{\fad(0,300)}who turned out to be Naeko Mi'ike-{\i1}san{\i0}, Officer Chiba's first love.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.54,0:00:35.97,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}We had at one point searched with Officer Chiba for the video letter she left at Teitan Primary School.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.97,0:00:42.35,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Officer Chiba apparently didn't notice that the policewoman before him was his first love,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.35,0:00:50.15,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}so we came up with a plan that involved pairing them together to investigate the break-ins.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.80,0:00:54.11,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}We figured that if they worked together, he'd be sure to notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.91,0:00:58.66,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Meanwhile, in the underground parking lot they entered to investigate,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.66,0:01:00.37,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}there was a rear-end collision.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.37,0:01:07.00,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Furthermore, the car that caused the collision had the word 'Die!' sprayed onto the windscreen from inside with red paint.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.99,0:01:11.30,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Was this caused by the same serial vandal?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.30,0:01:15.05,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}There were three people in the parking lot during the accident:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.05,0:01:20.14,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The driver of the rear-ended car: a company employee, Aketoshi Fukuchi-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.14,0:01:24.85,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The owner of the car that caused the accident: the housewife, Tokuko Shigei-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.85,0:01:29.56,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And a man waiting for his friend to come: a part-time worker, Takerō Meiwa-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.56,0:01:36.74,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Is the serial vandal, as well as the culprit of this collision, among these three?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.07,0:03:42.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Well then, here are the results!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.39,0:03:45.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}We throughly checked the parking lot,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.21,0:03:49.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}and there's nobody else here other than you three.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.52,0:03:53.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}This means one of you three did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.86,0:03:54.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.94,0:03:59.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}I was rear-ended! Why am I in the suspect list too?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.48,0:04:00.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Isn't it obvious?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.93,0:04:06.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}You could've smashed into your car on purpose and pretended to lose consciousness just to get out of the suspect list.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.52,0:04:09.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Give me a break...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.65,0:04:12.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}My wife and daughter are waiting for me at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.37,0:04:16.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}I've got to get dinner ready for my husband, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.05,0:04:19.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}If I don't get home soon, my parents are going to yell at me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.97,0:04:22.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}You actually care about your parents yelling at you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.95,0:04:26.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Yeah... They're both school teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.50,0:04:31.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Then, didn't they say anything about the flashy spoiler on your car?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.06,0:04:34.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}There's no way that'll pass a vehicle inspection!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.11,0:04:35.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}No...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.01,0:04:36.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}I kept it a secret from them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.94,0:04:42.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Come to think of it, the third car that was vandalised had a spoiler too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.65,0:04:44.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.06,0:04:47.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}But his car wasn't vandalised, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.56,0:04:49.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Why was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.06,0:04:50.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}How would I know?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.12,0:04:55.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}If it's about the flashiness, your car's spoiler is flashier.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.37,0:04:58.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}The wing's higher, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.66,0:05:03.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}If we could've looked more closely at the other vandalised cars, maybe we could've figured out something.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.88,0:05:08.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Then would you like to see the photos taken from other angles?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.17,0:05:10.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}I brought them with me in the mini patrol car parked outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.92,0:05:13.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Then I'll go get them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.06,0:05:14.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.10,0:05:17.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Hey, shouldn't you go with her, Chiba?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.38,0:05:19.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.09,0:05:22.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}If there's lots of photos it'll be hard to carry them all, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.77,0:05:25.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Helping ladies is a gentleman's duty!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.10,0:05:27.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Geez, you're so slow!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.50,0:05:29.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.65,0:06:05.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}What're you staring at each other like you're in some romantic comedy for?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.57,0:06:09.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Here. Hurry up and get those photos.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.54,0:06:11.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.41,0:06:13.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.65,0:06:17.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Don't ogle the newbie.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.64,0:06:19.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}'Ogle...?'
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.85,0:06:23.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}We should probably explain what's going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.80,0:06:24.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.15,0:06:27.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Honestly...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.32,0:06:32.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Huh? Those two are each other's first love,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.50,0:06:35.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}and Chiba-{\i1}kun{\i0} hasn't realised it yet?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.10,0:06:37.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}S-Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.21,0:06:39.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.20,0:06:41.57,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Hold on...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.79,0:06:44.37,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Miwako with Takagi-{\i1}kun{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.37,0:06:46.95,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and Shiratori-{\i1}kun{\i0} with Miss Kobayashi...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.95,0:06:48.53,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and then...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.95,0:06:54.54,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}if something happens and those two get together...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.54,0:06:56.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}See ya, Yumi!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.52,0:06:58.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be6}I must go.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.97,0:07:01.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be6}I'm leaving now!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.72,0:07:05.71,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I have to stop this...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.56,0:07:10.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}There certainly are photos from lots of different angles,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.24,0:07:14.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}but adding in my car, I can't find any common link between the victims' cars...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.35,0:07:17.86,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Could it be something like the mileage gauge? {Odometer?}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.86,0:07:20.85,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What was my car's reading...?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.85,0:07:24.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Um... Don't you remember...?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.72,0:07:26.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Not something like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.74,0:07:29.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}I guess you're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.53,0:07:34.56,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Huh? Did I just say that about the mileage gauge out loud?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.56,0:07:36.00,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Jerk...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.00,0:07:40.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Come on, let's hurry up and show Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0} the photos!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.56,0:07:43.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}That kid may notice something interesting again!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.67,0:07:47.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Yumi-{\i1}san{\i0}'s openly interfering now...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.03,0:07:49.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}It seems it had the opposite effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.22,0:07:53.80,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Indeed...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.63,0:07:58.51,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}the wing's lower than the spoiler on Meiwa-{\i1}san{\i0}'s car...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.51,0:08:00.23,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}so why was it targeted?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.24,0:08:06.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This is the 2nd vandalised car, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.36,0:08:09.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Yes, the car of a company employee returning from playing golf.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.36,0:08:12.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}How come there are so many golf bags?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.70,0:08:15.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Ah, it seems he was carrying his friends' bags too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.51,0:08:17.91,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Hold on...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.87,0:08:26.38,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.59,0:08:33.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Hey, have there been any traffic accidents involving children around here recently?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.89,0:08:35.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}There was one last month.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.75,0:08:40.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}I heard that a high school teacher caused the accident,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.40,0:08:44.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}but they admitted it was their fault, and settled out of court.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.77,0:08:47.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}What sort of car was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.11,0:08:49.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}An ordinary estate car.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.23,0:08:51.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Looks like they were on their way to an amusement park.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.40,0:08:55.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Since the car was packed full of rubber rings, beach balls,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.06,0:08:58.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}inflatable boats and so on.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.24,0:09:00.73,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I'm sure of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.73,0:09:04.37,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The vandal who tried to pry open the drivers' closed eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.62,0:09:08.25,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}...is that person!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.10,0:09:13.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}So, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.33,0:09:17.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Have you figured anything out from those photos yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.68,0:09:19.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Huh? Figured out what?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.64,0:09:26.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Like I said, who's the serial car vandal who sprayed 'Die!' in red paint
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.86,0:09:29.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}on that car's windscreen, drove it to try and escape,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.90,0:09:35.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}but ended up rear-ending the car in front,\Ntherefore abandoning the car and escaping?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.91,0:09:39.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}And since straight after the accident, the parking lot was sealed,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.53,0:09:41.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}the only three people in the parking lot were
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.48,0:09:45.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Fukuchi-{\i1}san{\i0}, who says he was driving the car that was rear-ended,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.86,0:09:51.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Shigei-{\i1}san{\i0}, who as well as having her car vandalised, also had it driven into Fukuchi-{\i1}san{\i0}'s car,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.11,0:09:56.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}and Meiwa-{\i1}san{\i0}, who claims to have been waiting for a friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.05,0:09:57.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Now, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.83,0:10:00.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Which one of them is the car vandal?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.80,0:10:03.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Even if you ask me, I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.87,0:10:05.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}I'm just a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.27,0:10:08.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}You're not just hiding it from me, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.23,0:10:11.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Hey, Yumi-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.32,0:10:13.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Um... the department store
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.48,0:10:16.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}are asking whether they can let customers into the parking lot yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.91,0:10:19.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}It can't be helped. Let them in.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.99,0:10:22.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Then can we go too?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.67,0:10:26.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}No way! The vandal is one of you three!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.16,0:10:27.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Then how about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.83,0:10:37.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Have those three go to the police station, and have Yumi-{\i1}san{\i0} ask them for their names, addresses, and the reasons they came here;
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.07,0:10:45.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}and have that policewoman deal with Officer Chiba, who had his car broken into before this happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.41,0:10:47.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.19,0:10:49.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Young ones should stay with their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.60,0:10:51.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}That's a good idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.23,0:10:52.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Agreed!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.52,0:10:54.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Yup, yup!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.28,0:10:56.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}W-Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.84,0:11:00.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}I'm off-duty today so I don't mind...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.55,0:11:02.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}I don't mind either...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.03,0:11:03.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}NO!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.79,0:11:07.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}You're in the Second Violent Crimes Investigation Division's Section 3, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.22,0:11:09.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Go off and chase some killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.16,0:11:10.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}But you told me to help out earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.88,0:11:14.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}That was then, this is now!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.34,0:11:17.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}She's interfering again.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.26,0:11:17.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.88,0:11:21.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Go tell the department store they can unseal the parking lot!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.70,0:11:22.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.87,0:11:25.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}And you're in the way, so hurry up and go home!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.74,0:11:26.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}In the way...?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.98,0:11:33.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Hey! Do you know anyone who prints painmobiles, Officer Chiba?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.27,0:11:34.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Yeah, I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.68,0:11:36.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}How long would it take to print one? {missing: 'at the quickest' but that just sounds so bad...}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.86,0:11:44.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Well, since it's somewhat like a sticker, if it's just one character in one window, I guess about 2 to 3 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.89,0:11:46.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.94,0:11:47.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.62,0:11:49.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Let me hear too!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.43,0:11:50.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Me too!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.28,0:11:51.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}And me too!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.25,0:11:54.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Yes, let them in.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.14,0:11:59.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}But please inform your customers that they can't pass through the site of the incident, so they have to detour around it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.26,0:12:02.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Umm, I passed along the message to the department store.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.97,0:12:05.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Then let's have those three come with me to the police station,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.61,0:12:09.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}and start taking their statements one by one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.93,0:12:13.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}In 2 to 3 hours...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.03,0:12:14.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}...it'll probably be over.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.91,0:12:28.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Hey, Takagi-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.57,0:12:31.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Do you know where my car keys are?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.58,0:12:33.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Ah, that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.20,0:12:35.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Yumi-{\i1}san{\i0} took them a while back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.70,0:12:37.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Yumi did?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.81,0:12:40.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}'Thanks, I'm off to do some decorating,' she said.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.87,0:12:42.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Decorating?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.26,0:12:46.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Don't tell me she's going to prank it by putting a weird sticker on it again!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.88,0:12:48.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Sticker?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.93,0:12:50.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Like those rookie drivers' stickers...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.63,0:12:54.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}...saying stuff like 'a rookie at love is driving'...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.13,0:13:00.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}The other day, I drove to a murder scene without realising that sticker was on there...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.73,0:13:02.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}It was embarrassing!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.98,0:13:10.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Well, if it's something like a 'rookie driver' magnet or sticker, you can easily take it off...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.62,0:14:08.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Hey! That's far enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.33,0:14:12.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Miwako'll get angry at me if you mess it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.84,0:14:14.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}We finally know...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.98,0:14:18.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}...what all the targeted cars have in common.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.36,0:14:22.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}The painmobile drawing in the first car...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.60,0:14:25.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}The golf bags in the second car...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.10,0:14:27.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}The spoiler in the third car...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.60,0:14:30.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}The toy boxes in the fourth car...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.36,0:14:35.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}And that FD, decorated like a painmobile.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.32,0:14:43.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Right. Every targeted car had its rear-window obstructed!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.08,0:14:47.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}And that's why Meiwa-{\i1}san{\i0}'s car wasn't targeted, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.56,0:14:54.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}It had a flashy spoiler, but it was so high that the rear-window wasn't blocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.88,0:15:03.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}And when you saw Fukuchi-{\i1}san{\i0} start up his car, with a ton of stuffed animals lined up in the rear-window, right in front of you...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.25,0:15:10.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}You rammed into his car with your own without even thinking about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.33,0:15:16.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Isn't that right, Tokuko Shigei-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.90,0:15:23.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}After you rear-ended him, you came to your senses...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.87,0:15:30.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}...and to try to absolve yourself, you sprayed 'Die!' on your own car to make it look like you were vandalised.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.37,0:15:37.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}You figured we'd think the vandal wouldn't vandalise their own car!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.14,0:15:40.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Did I get anything wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.86,0:15:53.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}There's no point in running!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.53,0:16:00.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}While you were being questioned by the police, we surrounded the entire area!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.64,0:16:07.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Right. This street goes from the train station to your house.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.66,0:16:11.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}In other words, we knew that after seeing this painmobile,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.11,0:16:16.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}you'd go and get the spray paint and lockpicks from your house and bring them here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.87,0:16:22.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Well, since this FD was a trap we set for you, we can overlook it...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.68,0:16:25.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}You're going to confess to the other ones, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.24,0:16:31.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}That you kept doing this for your son's sake, who died in a car accident last month...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.49,0:16:36.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}An accident caused by lack of caution...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.32,0:16:43.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}The field of vision for the rear-view mirror was obstructed by rubber rings and inflatable boats...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.03,0:16:50.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}...so unluckily, the driver didn't see you pushing your stroller behind their car.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.29,0:16:56.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}That's why you targeted every car that had its rear-window obstructed...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.68,0:17:00.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}...and wrote the word 'Die!' as punishment.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.14,0:17:14.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}What an unbearable case this turned out to be...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.23,0:17:21.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}To think that a victim of such an unfortunate accident would end up committing crimes...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.03,0:17:22.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.65,0:17:25.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}The regulations for rear-windows are pretty vague.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.52,0:17:28.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}There's no set legal limit...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.82,0:17:31.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}But Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}, how'd you figure it out?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.68,0:17:34.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}That Shigei-{\i1}san{\i0} had a son who'd died?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.37,0:17:39.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Because of the sunburn marks in the back seat of her car.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.46,0:17:42.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}I figured it out when I saw it in the parking lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.30,0:17:46.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}It's the mark for a child seat, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.25,0:17:52.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}If there's a mark like that in a car bought last year, then she must've had a child until last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.26,0:17:56.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}But she could've removed the seat because her child outgrew it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.76,0:18:00.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}If the child had recently needed a child seat, then that child would have to be younger than us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.73,0:18:07.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}And after being stuck in this long an investigation, wouldn't she be worried about that child?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.82,0:18:10.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Now that I think about it, she said...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.28,0:18:15.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I've got to get dinner ready for my husband, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.29,0:18:19.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}She was only worried about making dinner for her husband...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.38,0:18:23.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}That's right! Even though the man said his daughter was waiting for him...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.30,0:18:24.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.92,0:18:29.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}That's why she got so upset when I asked her if she had toys or anything like that in her car...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.55,0:18:33.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Right. Since she didn't need to buy that kind of stuff...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.14,0:18:39.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}But how did you know the old man had dolls lined up in his car?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.27,0:18:44.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Yeah. We saw he had lots of them scattered around on the back seat, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.78,0:18:47.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Because he said as much.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.58,0:18:51.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}'My daughter usually keeps them all neatly lined up so that they can be seen.'
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.43,0:18:57.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}The only way to do that was to put them behind the back seat, lined up against the rear-window.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.04,0:18:59.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.23,0:19:02.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}That's why she got so angry that she rammed into his car.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.88,0:19:08.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}There's no way she could've gone into a car to write 'Die!' in it if there was somebody inside...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.62,0:19:09.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.40,0:19:16.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Even if she couldn't write it, she at least wanted to open up the driver's field of vision,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.89,0:19:20.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}since the stuffed animals would fall out from the crash.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.34,0:19:23.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}But why was that car the only one with it written on the windscreen?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.90,0:19:29.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Up 'til now, all of the words were sprayed on the car ceilings, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.53,0:19:31.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Because of her lipstick.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.53,0:19:36.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Due to the shock, her face fell onto the airbag, and her lipstick got on it,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.69,0:19:40.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}so she tried to hide the lipstick mark with the same-colour spray paint.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.32,0:19:44.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}She wanted to make it look like it was an extension of the message.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.96,0:19:49.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Though, if her lipstick was on the airbag, then so was her saliva,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.89,0:19:53.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}so the vandal's identity could be uncovered with DNA analysis.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.34,0:19:55.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Then even without this trap...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.51,0:19:59.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}No. This was the right thing to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.08,0:20:07.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Because we don't want her to commit more of these sad crimes...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.52,0:20:10.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Hey, Yumi-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.44,0:20:12.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}I'm going home now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.40,0:20:13.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.40,0:20:16.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}We'll probably have to do questioning after this, so bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.46,0:20:20.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Well, I guess I should tell Miwako I borrowed her car...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.44,0:20:27.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}See you later, Officer Chiba.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.12,0:20:28.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.63,0:20:44.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Oh, right. I have to take Miwako's FD back to the Police HQ, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.02,0:20:46.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Take the mini patrol car back, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.66,0:20:48.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.12,0:20:52.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Since it's on the way, how about you give Chiba-{\i1}kun{\i0} a ride home?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.46,0:20:53.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.36,0:21:00.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Somehow, I feel like I'm being arrested. Makes me kind of nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.70,0:21:04.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}It's the first time I've been in a mini patrol car, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.09,0:21:05.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.91,0:21:07.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Though...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.99,0:21:12.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Though it doesn't feel like it's the first time...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.30,0:21:14.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}...that I met you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.99,0:21:20.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Sorry if I'm wrong, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.98,0:21:23.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Would you happen to be...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.77,0:21:27.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.23,0:22:50.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Would you happen to be...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.98,0:22:52.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.32,0:22:58.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}The one who gave me a parking ticket in Haido City a while back?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.32,0:23:01.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.23,0:23:03.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}I transferred to HQ last month.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.54,0:23:08.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}I knew I'd recognised you from somewhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.04,0:23:10.79,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}So that's where it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.79,0:23:15.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Officer Chiba's still totally clueless.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.50,0:23:18.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.33,0:23:21.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Even after Yumi-{\i1}san{\i0} gave them a break...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.34,0:23:22.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.26,0:23:24.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Should've known. 'Pearls before swine' and all. {this is actually LTIL}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.72,0:23:26.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}Hey, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.52,0:23:28.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}More like 'coins before cats.' {this is the correct japanese equivalent to pearls before swine}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.08,0:23:49.00,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Nah... couldn't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.87,0:23:53.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Hey!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.10,0:23:55.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}What's with {\i1}this{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.86,0:23:58.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}{\fad(0,300)}Please don't get angry...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.84,0:24:00.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2}
